     <div type="explanation_of_frontispiece">
   <pb facs="11"/>
   <head>THE EXPLANATION of the Frontispice.</head>
   <l>IT was when Industry did sleepe</l>
   <l>The Wolfe was Tutor to the Sheepe,</l>
   <l>And to amaze a plainer man,</l>
   <l>The thiefe was made the guardian.</l>
   <l>But can a Wolfe forget to prey?</l>
   <l>Can Night be lightened into Day?</l>
   <l>Without respect of lawes or blood,</l>
   <l>His charge he makes to be his food.</l>
   <l>With that triumphant he sits downe,</l>
   <l>Opprest, not honour'd with a Crowne,</l>
   <l>And on the lesser beasts does try</l>
   <l>A most Authenticke Tyranny:</l>
   <l>This the French Lyon heares, and when</l>
   <l>He's thought fast sleeping in his denne,</l>
   <l>Vengeance and He at once doe wake,</l>
   <l>And on the Wolfe their fury flake.</l>
   <l>Bad acts may bloome somtimes, but n'er grow high,</l>
   <l>Nor doe they live so sure, as they shall dye.</l>
   <pb facs="12"/>
